;
in this state of preservation the species could be considered common. Apart from the holotype , studied specimens include: from Turin Hill , NMS G.1881.5.60, NMS G.1885.54.6B, NMS G.1887.35.6A, NMS G.1891.92.236, NMS G.1891.92.238, NMS G.1891.92.275, NMS G.
